high_level.notes: STM32H753xI is a 32-bit Arm Cortex-M7 MCU running at up to 480 MHz with 2MB dual-bank flash, 1MB RAM, hardware crypto acceleration (AES, HASH, HMAC, True RNG), and extensive peripheral set including Ethernet, USB HS/FS, FDCAN, LCD-TFT controller, JPEG codec, 3x 16-bit ADC, 2x 12-bit DAC, and up to 168 GPIOs. The MCU features three power domains (D1/D2/D3) with independent clock gating, multiple low-power modes, and operates from 1.62V to 3.6V supply.

VSS.name: VSS
VSS.description: Ground return. Connect all VSS pins to the ground plane for proper device operation. (42 pins across packages.)

VDD.name: VDD
VDD.description: Digital power supply. Connect all VDD pins to the supply rail with adequate decoupling capacitors (100nF ceramic per pin minimum, plus 4.7uF bulk). (27 pins across packages.)

VCAP.name: VCAP
VCAP.description: Internal voltage regulator output capacitor connection. Connect a 4.7uF low-ESR ceramic capacitor between VCAP and VSS. (3 pins across packages.)

VBAT.name: VBAT
VBAT.description: Battery backup supply. Supplies the RTC, backup registers, and backup SRAM when VDD is not present. Connect to VDD if backup not needed. Range: 1.65V to 3.6V.

VSSA.name: VSSA
VSSA.description: Analog ground reference. Connect to the ground plane star point near VDDA decoupling.

VREF-.name: VREF-
VREF-.description: ADC negative reference voltage. Must be connected to VSSA.

VREF+.name: VREF+
VREF+.description: ADC/DAC positive reference voltage. Can be connected to VDDA or to an external reference. Range: 1.62V to VDDA.

VDDA.name: VDDA
VDDA.description: Analog power supply for ADC, DAC, OPAMP, COMP, and VREFBUF. Must be equal to or greater than VDD. Range: 1.62V to 3.6V. Decouple with 1uF + 10nF ceramic capacitors.

VDDLDO.name: VDDLDO
VDDLDO.description: Supply voltage for the internal LDO regulator. Range: 1.62V to 3.6V. When not available on a package, internally tied to VDD.

VDD50US_B.name: VDD50US B
VDD50US_B.description: USB 5V sensing/power supply pin. When not available on a package, internally tied to VDD33USB.

VDD33US_B.name: VDD33US B
VDD33US_B.description: USB 3.3V power supply for internal USB PHY. Range: 3.0V to 3.6V. Connect to 3.3V supply when USB is used, or tie to VSS/leave floating when USB is not used.
